I"‰<p>Steps I‚Äôve been following to set up my new M1 mac book air, and the issues I encounter - mainly because of incompatibilities with packages that are not yet updated.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Install Xcode and Command Line tools, this takes the longest.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Install Homebrew:</p>

    <pre>
 /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install.sh)"
 </pre>

    <p>Add Homebrew to PATH:</p>

    <pre>
 echo 'eval "$(/opt/homebrew/bin/brew shellenv)"' &gt;&gt; /Users/camilaburne/.zprofile
 eval "$(/opt/homebrew/bin/brew shellenv)"
 </pre>

    <p>Then check if it can run with:</p>

    <pre>
 brew ‚Äîversion
 </pre>
  </li>
  <li>Install GIT:
    <pre>
 brew install git
 </pre>

    <p>Then, <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/github/authenticating-to-github/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/adding-a-new-ssh-key-to-your-github-account">authenticate via SSH to Github</a> so you can connect to your repos.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Unhide files with shift+command+dot and sudo chflags nohidden, and open my bash profile file just to check it out :)</p>

    <pre>
 sudo chflags nohidden /Library/ ~/Library/

 user@Camilas-Air ~ % touch . bash_profile
 user@Camilas-Air ~ % open . bash_profile
 </pre>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Install Python3 <a href="https://opensource.com/article/19/5/python-3-default-mac">the ‚Äúright‚Äù way</a>, without removing python 2.7 https://opensource.com/article/19/5/python-3-default-mac just install python 3, pip 3, and manage with pyenv</p>
  </li>
  <li>Install <a href="https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv#understanding-path">pyenv</a>, pipx, <a href="https://pipenv.pypa.io/en/latest/install/">pipenv</a>.
 pyenv instructions from its github repo
    <pre>
 brew update
 brew install pyenv
 </pre>

    <p>pipenv instructions from pipenv website</p>
    <pre>
 pip install --user pipx
 pipx install pipenv
 </pre>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Installed jupyterlab with pipenv.</p>
  </li>
  <li>Install ruby Jekyll</li>
</ol>

